events.name: GDG DevFest Thunder Bay - 2019
events.description:
We are extremely excited to announce our very first DevFest 2019 event here in Thunder bay!!!!!!

Our DevFest event is a community associated one day event for bringing everyone together to learn and discuss about latest tech like I.O.T, Firebase, Flutter,etc. A great place to sharpen your skills and discuss with world renown Google Developer Experts, Women Techmakers and specialists.

Don't be fooled by the name... this event is for anyone who is interested in learning about new emerging technologies.

Agenda:
8:00 AM - 8:30 AM: Attendees Settling in & Networking.
8:30 AM - 9:15 AM: Breakfast
9:15 AM - 9:30 AM: Introduction of Google Developer Group (GDG) Cloud Thunder Bay & Women in Tech.
9:30 AM - 10:45 AM: Build Cross Platform Apps With Flutter By Faisal Abid(Google Developer Expert)
10:45 AM - 11:15 AM: Ice Breaker 1 & Win prizes, Snacks.
11:15 AM - 12:30 PM: IT career in Regards to Diversity and Inclusion By Erica Silva (Women Techmakers)
12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch
1:30 PM - 2:45 PM: AI,Machine Learning and their Applications By Ekaba Bisong(Google Developer Expert).
2:45 PM - 3:15 PM: Ice Breaker 2 & Win prizes.
3:15 PM - 4:30 PM: Google Security & IoT DB By Kevin A. McGrail (Google Developer Expert).
4:30 PM - 5:00 PM: Snacks, Coffee & Group Photo.

So mark your calendars for 28th September, 2019

Location for the event: 1001, ATAC Building, Lakehead University, Thunder Bay, ON, Canada - (P7B 5E1).

12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch & Networking
1:30 PM - 3:30 PM: Hands-on Lab ML - Contd.
3:30 PM - 4:00 PM: Completion Badges and PRIZES!!
4:00 PM - 5:00 PM: WTM and Networking
